label.value: medial ocellar retinula cell

value.value: Any ocellar retinula cell (FBbt:00004242) that overlaps some medial ocellus (FBbt:00004507).

label.value: medial ocellar ganglion

value.value: Detached ganglion that sits below the medial ocellus and contains the axonal projections of the medial retinula cells (Caldwell et al., 2007; Scheffer et al., 2020).

label.value: lateral ocellar ganglion

value.value: Detached ganglion that sits below a lateral ocellus and contains the axonal projections of the lateral retinula cells (Caldwell et al., 2007; Scheffer et al., 2020).

label.value: ocellar ganglion interneuron type 01

value.value: Ocellar interneuron with a large diameter (Caldwell et al., 2007; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). There are four of these per ganglion, totaling twelve per organism (Caldwell et al., 2007; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). They collectively tile all three ocellar ganglia in each organism (Dorkenwald et al., 2024).

label.value: ocellar ganglion interneuron type 02

value.value: Ocellar interneuron with a smaller diameter (Dorkenwald et al., 2024). There are eight of these cells per organism (Dorkenwald et al., 2024).

label.value: ocellar ganglion local neuron

value.value: Local neuron of the ocellar ganglia (Dorkenwald et al., 2024). It is a small neuron that connects sparsely with photoreceptors from all ocelli (Dorkenwald et al., 2024). There are approximately 16 of these per organism (Dorkenwald et al., 2024).

label.value: lateral ocellar ganglion interneuron type 01

value.value: Ocellar ganglion interneuron type 01 that receives input in a lateral ocellar ganglion (Dorkenwald et al., 2024). There are four of these per lateral ocellar ganglion (Dorkenwald et al., 2024).

label.value: medial ocellar ganglion interneuron type 01

value.value: Ocellar ganglion interneuron type 01 that receives input in a medial ocellar ganglion (Dorkenwald et al., 2024). There are four of these per medial ocellar ganglion (Dorkenwald et al., 2024).

label.value: ocellar centrifugal neuron

value.value: Centrifugal neuron with dendrites in the brain and an axon that projects to an ocellar ganglion, providing feedback to the ocellar interneurons (Dorkenwald et al., 2024). There are approximately 25 of these per brain (Dorkenwald et al., 2024).

label.value: DPMm2 lineage neuron

value.value: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that develops from some neuroblast DPMm2 (FBbt:00100584).

label.value: neuroblast CP5

value.value: Type I neuroblast of the brain that produces a secondary lineage with somas posterolateral to the lateral horn and arbors in the lateral horn and posterior superior protocerebrum (Schlegel et al., 2024).

label.value: CP5 lineage neuron

value.value: Any neuron (FBbt:00005106) that develops from some neuroblast CP5 (FBbt:00052820).

label.value: lobula plate intrinsic neuron LPi1-2

value.value: Intrinsic neuron of the lobula plate that has its synaptic terminals throughout, but restricted to lobula plate layers 1 and 2, receiving input in layer 1 and sending output to layer 2 (Shinomiya et al., 2022). The majority of its input is from T4a and T5a cells (Shinomiya et al., 2022). It has its soma in the lobula plate cell body rind (Shinomiya et al., 2022). There are two of these cells per optic lobe and they tile the lobula plate in a jigsaw-like pattern (Matsliah et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024).

label.value: lobula plate intrinsic neuron LPi2-1

value.value: Intrinsic neuron of the lobula plate that has its synaptic terminals mainly restricted to lobula plate layers 1 and 2, receiving input in layer 2 and sending output to layer 1 (Shinomiya et al., 2022). The majority of its input is from T4b and T5b cells (Shinomiya et al., 2022).

label.value: lobula plate columnar neuron LPC2

value.value: Lobula plate columnar neuron that has its main dendritic arborization in lobula plate layer 3 and receives input from T4c and T5c neurons (Shinomiya et al., 2022).

label.value: lobula-lobula plate columnar neuron LLPC2

value.value: Lobula-lobula plate columnar neuron with its lobula plate arborization mainly in layer 3 (Shinomiya et al., 2022).

label.value: lobula-lobula plate columnar neuron LLPC3

value.value: Lobula-lobula plate columnar neuron with its lobula plate arborization mainly in layer 4 (Shinomiya et al., 2022).

label.value: lobula plate tangential neuron Lpt13a

value.value: Lobula plate tangential neuron that has presynapses in lobula plate layers 1 and 3 (Shinomiya et al., 2022). Its axon projects to the central brain (Shinomiya et al., 2022).

label.value: lobula plate tangential neuron LPT/LPi2a

value.value: Lobula plate tangential neuron that has postsynapses and presynapses mainly in lobula plate layer 2, with some sparser processes in layer 1 (Shinomiya et al., 2022). It receives strong input from T4b and T5b neurons (Shinomiya et al., 2022). It projects to the central brain (Shinomiya et al., 2022).

label.value: lobula plate intrinsic neuron LPi2b

value.value: Large lobula plate intrinsic neuron that spans the entirety of layer 2, with little arborization in other layers (Shinomiya et al., 2022).

label.value: lobula plate intrinsic neuron LPi34-12

value.value: Lobula plate intrinsic neuron that receives input in layers 3 and 4 and sends output to layers 1 and 2 (Shinomiya et al., 2022).

label.value: transmedullary Y neuron TmY16

value.value: Transmedullary Y neuron with a broad arbor in the proximal medulla and lobula plate arborization mainly in layers 3-4 (Shinomiya et al., 2022).
